radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung bases show basilar subsegmental atelectasis. The appendix is dilated, hyperemic and surrounded by marked periappendiceal fat stranding and fluid. The cecum is hyperemic. The liver enhances homogeneously with no focal liver lesions. The stomach and small bowel loops are unremarkable. The bladder is underdistended. There is no free pelvic fluid and no pelvic or inguinal adenopathy.
